        <div class="bot_says_game rounded-lg" id="bot_says_game">  <!--the class for this div is in the app.css-->
            <!--<h10>potatoe</h10>-->
                <div class='container border border-danger float-right rounded-lg' style='border-width:4px !important; background-color: #ffe0dd;'>
                    <h4>Welcome to the game!</h4>
                    <br>
                    <h5>The way the game works is by giving you some explaination of an object/class. You then get a table were to type in the correspoding attributes and 
                    methods. Keep in mind we are using C++ as our language! So any standard data types and data structures should be written with the correct syntax.</h5>
                    <br>
                    <h5>This is more of an arcade game! So try and try to get the highest score! If you don't get enough of an answer right you will get a life deducted and a few 
                    points. You can only get more difficult questions if you get the majority of a question right. </h5>
                    <br>
                    <h5>We do use audio cues to show how close to completely right you were. For completely right:<button type="button" class="btn btn-success"  onClick='audioGood()'>Good!</button>
                    For almost there: <button type="button" class="btn btn-info"  onClick='audioOkay()'>Okay.</button> Lastly for being really wrong:<button type="button" class="btn btn-danger" onClick='audioBad()'>Bad.</button></h5>
                    
                </div><br>
                
                <div class='container border border-primary float-left rounded-lg' style='border-width:6px !important; background-color: #e4e7ff;'>
